comment:
* Detailed description of a {@link DeviceState} that includes separated sets of
     * {@link DeviceStateProperties} for properties that correspond to the state of the system when
     * the device is in this state, as well as physical properties that describe this state.
     *
     * Instantiation of this class should only be done by the system server, and clients of
     * {@link DeviceStateManager} will receive {@link DeviceState} objects.
     *
     * @see DeviceStateManager
     * @hide

variables.name: mIdentifier
variables.comment: Unique identifier for the device state.

variables.name: mName
variables.comment: String description of the device state.

variables.name: mSystemProperties
variables.comment: {@link ArraySet} of system properties that apply to this state.

variables.name: mPhysicalProperties
variables.comment: {@link ArraySet} of physical device properties that apply to this state.

methods.name: public int getIdentifier()
methods.comment: Returns the unique identifier for the device state.

methods.name: public String getName()
methods.comment: Returns a string description of the device state.

methods.name: public Set<@SystemDeviceStateProperties Integer> getSystemProperties()
methods.comment: Returns the {@link Set} of system properties that apply to this state.

methods.name: public Set<@DeviceStateProperties Integer> getPhysicalProperties()
methods.comment: Returns the {@link Set} of physical device properties that apply to this state.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
